Enoch Mpianzi's mother believes that Parktown Boy's High failed her son. She believes irresponsibility led to a school camp taking a tragic turn last week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Enoch Mpianzi's, Anto mother believes that Parktown Boy's High School failed her son. She believes irresponsibility led to a school camp taking a tragic turn last week. The 13-year-old boy died during the orientation camp. Enoch Mpianzi's father: I need justice for my son “When we send our children to school, we have that hope to say that we give them to good hands but some people prove us that they are not capable...” she added. The South African Human Rights Commission has indicated that it would legally help the family of Mpianzi.